thread.title: California’s Quirky Primary System Poses Threat to Democrats on a Crammed Ballot

author: Alejandro Lazo
title: California’s Quirky Primary System Poses Threat to Democrats on a Crammed Ballot
text:
In a crowded field of Democrats vying to flip a Republican congressional seat in Orange County, Calif., this year, Jay Chen’s chances looked promising.
The naval intelligence officer and community-college trustee had garnered the most votes among local Democratic committee and club members in a January caucus, and racked up endorsements from local elected officials.
But...
